Well, hello everybody.  Doc I saw your invite at 27 and decided to respond.  But honestly, visiting you guys on this site is almost like being back &quot;in country&quot;.  There's no doubt in my mind I'm going to have &quot;in coming&quot; as a result of this communication.  I agree that this site is a national asset and should be preserved.  Interestingly, I lost the site as a result of renewing my computer's hardware and I'll be doggone, but I couldn't find it again.  I used every trick in the book to search for the site and failed.  Two weeks I looked for this site.  Finally, I contacted other vet organizations on the net and one of them gave me the URL again.  If you try to find this site using the search engines out there my experience is you might not be successful.  This seems to be a function of &quot;advertisement/money&quot;.  I would recommend that we get this site more exposed and let all veterans know about it.  Probably the easiest way is to get the women involved.  Okay, that's it.  What have I done to myself?  Corbin
